so I'm just gonna come right out with it.

162
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:19,480
月度报告送回总部了
The monthly report's back to HQ.

163
00:13:19,640 --> 00:13:22,320
我建议他们把你安排到别的地方
I'm recommending they post you somewhere else.

164
00:13:23,320 --> 00:13:25,000
为什么?
Why?

165
00:13:25,160 --> 00:13:27,680
有人把机密情报泄露给英国人
Someone's leaking confidential reports to the Brits.

166
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:30,480
我们跟军情六处互相交换信息啊
Well, we talk to MI6, they talk to us.

167
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:32,560
我们给的情报他们都已经知道了
We give them stuff that they already know.

168
00:13:32,680 --> 00:13:34,560
除了越南的事
Not on Vietnam.

169
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:36,160
那份国家安全委员会
That National Security Council report

170
00:13:36,280 --> 00:13:37,760
在周二午餐会议上的报告?
on the Tuesday lunch meetings?

171
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:38,760
没错
Mm-hmm.

172
00:13:38,920 --> 00:13:40,617
总部只发给了亚洲分部 
HQ sent it only to the offices in Asia. 

173
00:13:40,618 --> 00:13:42,160
但现在伦敦的人也有了
Now London has it.

174
00:13:42,320 --> 00:13:45,400
那也可能是从别的分部发过去的
Well, that could have come from any of those offices.

175
00:13:45,520 --> 00:13:48,480
但不是的
But it didn't.

176
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:49,960
重要的不是你这么做了
It's not that you did it.

177
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:52,160
而是他拿什么威胁你让你这么做的
It's whatever he's got on you that made you do it.

178
00:13:52,280 --> 00:13:55,560
你已经妥协了 我不能用你了
You're compromised. I can't use you.

179
00:13:57,520 --> 00:13:59,600
每个人都有过分的时候 哈里森
Everyone crosses the line, Harrison,

180
00:13:59,760 --> 00:14:01,200
但重要的是 每当你回头看
but it's important when you look back

181
00:14:01,320 --> 00:14:02,800
至少你知道自己在干什么
you can at least still see it.

182
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:06,400
不管结果怎样 我希望你记住这一点
I hope you remember that, wherever you end up.

183
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:42,880
- 你好 弗兰克 - 我来跟你决斗
- G'day, Frank. - I came here to fight you.

184
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,720
你在说什么呢?
What are you talking about?

185
00:14:44,880 --> 00:14:46,960
我知道你觉得很荒谬
I'm sure you think that's ridiculous.

186
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:49,040
但如果这是一个公平的世界
But if this was any sort of just world

187
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:52,040
有个男人爱着自己的妻子 照顾她
where a man who loved his wife and took care of her

188
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:54,040
从没想过妻子会背叛自己
and never, ever dreamed of cheating on her,

189
00:14:54,160 --> 00:14:56,280
而另一个男人...
and another man...

190
00:14:58,560 --> 00:15:01,160
如果这是一个公平的世界
If this was any sort of just world,

191
00:15:01,320 --> 00:15:04,320
我会跟你决斗 并打败你
I would fight you and I would beat you.

192
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:06,840
然而在这个世界 像你这样的男人赢了
In this world, a man like you wins that fight.

193
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:11,480
像你这样的男人... 怎么了?
A man like you with... what?

194
00:15:13,240 --> 00:15:16,280
你有什么好的能让我老婆选择你?
What have you got that my wife chooses you over me?

195
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:23,800
周五晚上 我们会永远离开新加坡
Friday night, we're leaving Singapore for good.

196
00:15:23,960 --> 00:15:27,280
我们会乘船去欧洲 再也不回来了
We're going to Europe by ship and we're not coming back.

197
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:30,400
我理解
I understand.

198
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:33,640
不 你不理解
No, you really don't.

199
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:38,280
我要你在我们离开之前去见她 
I want you to go to her before we leave. 

200
00:15:38,281 --> 00:15:40,360
我要你跟她说清楚
I want you to make your case.

201
00:15:42,720 --> 00:15:47,480
如果你爱着她 想让她一直快乐的话
If you love her in a way that will care for her forever,

202
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:49,080
你跟她说清楚
you tell her that.

203
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:52,120
弗兰克 我不会去的...
Frank, I'm not gonna...

204
00:15:52,280 --> 00:15:54,720
如果克莱尔的心还在这儿的话
I'm not gonna spend the rest of my life with Claire

205
00:15:54,840 --> 00:15:57,120
我是不会跟她共度余生的
if part of her never leaves here.

206
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,760
如果她选择了你 那她就跟你走
If she chooses you, she chooses you.

207
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:09,880
周五晚上之前你还有时间
You've got till Friday night.

208
00:16:18,280 --> 00:16:22,320
- 詹姆斯・林 - 你对他了解有多少?
- James Lim. - What do you know about him?

209
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:27,480
我以为我们之间已经说清楚了
I thought our arrangement was clear.

210
00:16:27,640 --> 00:16:30,080
当我问你要东西的时候 你就给我
When I ask you for something, I get it.

211
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:34,040
我不记得还说过要交换条件
I don't recall there being any quid pro quo.

212
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:37,800
现在不管你跟我老板说什么都不重要了
Right now it doesn't matter what you tell my boss

213
00:16:37,920 --> 00:16:39,840
因为他就要炒掉我了
because he's about to terminate me.

214
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,931
所以我想要你的信息... 
So what I need from you... 

215
00:16:41,932 --> 00:16:43,120
是想找到他的把柄
I need some dirt on him

216
00:16:43,240 --> 00:16:45,160
这样他们就会炒了他而不是我
so they get rid of him instead of me.

217
00:16:46,520 --> 00:16:49,920
为什么你会特别选择詹姆斯・林?
What made you choose James Lim in particular?

218
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:51,720
山姆・卡拉汉想要了解他
Sam Callaghan wanted to know about him.

219
00:16:51,880 --> 00:16:54,040
可我去找资料的时候 什么都没有
When I went to look at the file, the file's missing.

220
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:56,440
唯一能拿到的资料就是... 怀尔德・比尔
The only one with access to that... Wild Bill.

221
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:58,657
如果他在忙什么...  
So if he's up to something...  

222
00:16:58,658 --> 00:17:00,200
对啊 他现在忙死了
Oh, yes. He's up to his neck.

223
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:02,960
这对我来说有什么好处?
But what's in it for me?

224
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:07,400
华盛顿
Washington.

225
00:17:07,560 --> 00:17:10,520
我没有把安委会文件里的东西都给你
I didn't give you everything that was in that NSC file.

226
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:13,320
现在 如果你想要给你老板剩下的资料
Now, if you're the guy that tells your bosses the rest,

227
00:17:13,480 --> 00:17:16,308
告诉他们总统办公室里有哪些人 
tell them who's in the room with the President, 

228
00:17:16,309 --> 00:17:17,440
谁是他的亲信
who's got his ear,

229
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:21,240
你会拿到本土调动的 我保证
you get that stateside transfer you want, guaranteed.

230
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:25,960
好啊 成交
Alright. I'm in.

231
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:31,040
差点忘了 还有一件事
Oh, I almost forgot. There's one more thing.

232
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:36,120
我要跟苏玲有关的所有资料 
I want the files on Su Ling. All copies.

233
00:17:36,240 --> 00:17:38,680
我的天!
My, my!

234
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:43,840
宝贝小熊真的长大了 对吗?
Baby Bear really has grown up, hasn't he?

235
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:45,730
哈里森先生来电话了 
Mr Harrison called. 

236
00:17:45,731 --> 00:17:47,720
说没有詹姆斯・林的资料
He said there was no file on James Lim.

237
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:50,240
扯淡 詹姆斯・林想要参与政治
That's bullshit. James Lim wants to get into politics.

238
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:52,920
天啊 他哥哥是被捕的工会领导
For God's sake, his brother's a jailed trade union leader

239
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:54,400
被指控参与炸弹袭击
accused of bombings.

240
00:17:54,560 --> 00:17:56,373
他们连街上扫地的人的资料都有  
They've got files on streetsweepers.  

241
00:17:56,374 --> 00:17:57,280
他知道你会这么说
He knew you'd say that.

242
00:17:57,440 --> 00:18:00,000
他说他们没有你想象的那么多情报来源
He said to say they don't have as many tentacles as you think.

243
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:01,120
我不相信他的话  
Well, I don't believe him.  

244
00:18:01,121 --> 00:18:02,080
他为什么要撒谎呢?
Why would he lie?

245
00:18:02,240 --> 00:18:04,360
所以整个新加坡
So he's the one man in the whole of Singapore

246
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:06,160
中情局唯一缺少他的文件?
the CIA doesn't have a file on?

247
00:18:06,280 --> 00:18:07,680
他已经解释啦
Like he said.

248
00:18:19,320 --> 00:18:22,440
阿姨 该停手了
Aunty, it's a sign to stop.

249
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:30,240
是么 它们只是鸟而已啊
Oh, yeah, they're just birds.

250
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:32,475
她要的话我随时帮她弄些 还能算便宜点 
I can get her some more, for cheap too. 

251
00:18:32,476 --> 00:18:33,240
弄只鸭也没问题
Maybe even throw in a duck.

252
00:18:33,360 --> 00:18:34,760
再跟我说下整件事
Explain the whole thing to me again.

253
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:36,480
温斯顿当时在查詹姆斯・林
Winston was investigating James Lim.

254
00:18:36,640 --> 00:18:39,280
我不知道他查到什么 但已经足以被灭口
I don't know what he found, but it was enough to get him killed.

255
00:18:42,980 --> 00:18:44,980
钥匙 在哪里?

256
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:48,400
现在可能不太方便上去吧...
Maybe now's not such a good time to...

257
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:51,400
钥匙 在哪里?

258
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:05,480
林先生 一切可好?
Everything alright, Mr Lim?

259
00:19:31,320 --> 00:19:34,320
那是李库方吧?
Oh. That was Lee Kum Fong?

260
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:38,600
他究竟要什么?
What the hell was he after?

261
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:41,200
我不知道 他刚在喊什么钥匙之类的
I don't know. He was saying something about a key.

262
00:19:49,240 --> 00:19:51,880
喔 喔 算了吧
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa. Forget it.

263
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:53,360
他妈的
Come on.

264
00:19:57,320 --> 00:19:59,680
怎么都弄不开这玩意
Never going to get this sucker open.

265
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:01,160
是啊
Nope.

266
00:20:06,760 --> 00:20:09,720
- 你跟周怡在一块多久了? - 啥?
- How long have you been with Joo Ee? - Huh?

267
00:20:09,840 --> 00:20:11,800
你觉得她就是你要找的吗?
Do you think she's the one?

268
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:16,560
兄弟 我要一辈子跟她在一起
Uh... I'm with that girl for life, man.

269
00:20:16,720 --> 00:20:19,000
- 是么? - 是啊
-Yeah? - Yeah.

270
00:20:19,120 --> 00:20:20,680
可你们俩就只会吵架啊
All you do is argue.

271
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:23,591
是啊 她爱喝酒 我爱赌博 
Sure. She drinks too much. I gamble too much. 

272
00:20:23,592 --> 00:20:25,920
她吼我 我们就打起来了
She yells at me. We fight.

273
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:28,400
我有的选么?
What's the alternative?

274
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:31,680
没她的日子 算了吧 
A life without her. Forget it, man.

275
00:20:31,840 --> 00:20:34,960
世上只有一个周怡 我喜欢她 就喜欢她一个
There's only one Joo Ee, and I like her. There's nobody else.

276
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:45,880
妈的
Shit.

277
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:48,240
我想到了
I got an idea.

278
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:53,760
康我不懂这个
I don't know about this, Kang.

279
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:55,480
你觉不觉得我们放太多了?
You don't think we're using too much?

280
00:20:55,640 --> 00:20:57,760
留着用来干嘛?
What else am I going to use this for?

281
00:20:57,880 --> 00:20:59,280
别想太多啦
Yeah, don't think so much.

282
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:44,880
火灭了 它为什么会灭?
It went out. Why did it go out?

283
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:47,520
烂导线
Stupid old fuse.

284
00:21:57,480 --> 00:21:58,960
康!
Kang!

285
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:02,280
康 你还好吗?
Kang, are you alright?

286
00:22:05,880 --> 00:22:08,200
- 啊... - 你还好吧?
- Oh... - You're alright, yeah?

287
00:22:08,360 --> 00:22:09,920
听得到我说话吗?
You hear me?

288
00:22:10,040 --> 00:22:11,400
嘿 嘿 嘿 嘿
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

289
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:16,080
还真炸开了 你个疯子
That opened it, you bloody lunatic.

290
00:22:17,360 --> 00:22:20,760
钱我能留着吧?
I can keep the money, right?

291
00:22:20,920 --> 00:22:22,960
- 反正它们的主人已经死了 - 啥?
- It belongs to a dead man. - Huh?

292
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:33,680
今天真走运!
Today must be my lucky day.

293
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:53,040
这肯定是温斯顿的文件
There's no doubt it's Winston's file.

294
00:22:57,120 --> 00:22:59,320
温斯顿叔叔说过
Uncle Winston used to say,

295
00:22:59,480 --> 00:23:04,360
欲速则不达 照片它可不会着急
'No fuss, no rush. The picture won't hurry because you do.'

296
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:15,240
这张没什么
Nothing here.

297
00:23:28,400 --> 00:23:32,560
- 这张也没有 - 拜托 我们要看到脸
- Nope. This one either. - Come on. We need a face.

298
00:23:34,560 --> 00:23:36,320
下一张看起来有点不同
The next ones look different.

299
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:11,360
他是...
Is that...

300
00:24:39,520 --> 00:24:41,440
怀尔德・比尔
Wild Bill.

301
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:45,680
詹姆斯・林... 在和中情局的人秘密会面
James Lim... is having a secret meeting with the CIA.

302
00:24:45,840 --> 00:24:48,360
我不需要 谢谢 谢谢
No, not for me, thank you. Thank you.

303
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:56,440
康拉德骗了你
Conrad lied to you.

304
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:03,680
詹姆斯・林是中情局的线人
James Lim's a CIA informant.

305
00:25:03,800 --> 00:25:05,360
一定有他的文件的
There's got to be a file on him.

306
00:25:05,480 --> 00:25:06,840
你肯定找到了的
You must have found it.

307
00:25:07,840 --> 00:25:10,040
- 事情没那么简单 - 就这么简单
- It's not that simple. - Yes, it is.

308
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:12,440
詹姆斯・林为中情局卖力 对吧?
James Lim works for the CIA, yes or no?

309
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:14,200
- 不是 - 好吧
- No. - Alright.

310
00:25:14,360 --> 00:25:16,280
我要把所有事告诉阿姆兰
I'm going to take this whole thing to Amran.

311
00:25:16,440 --> 00:25:18,560
新加坡警察对于中情局涉及谋杀
The Singaporean police would be most interested

312
00:25:18,720 --> 00:25:20,120
一个正直的中国良民之事
in the CIA's involvement in the murder

313
00:25:20,240 --> 00:25:21,920
肯定十分感兴趣
of an upstanding Chinese citizen.

314
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:25,840
詹姆斯・林不是为中情局做事
James Lim did not work for the CIA.

315
00:25:25,960 --> 00:25:27,440
他是为怀尔德・比尔做事
He was working for Wild Bill.

316
00:25:27,600 --> 00:25:29,880
胡说 怀尔德・比尔甚至都不负责那个领域
Bullshit. Wild Bill doesn't even work in the field.

317
00:25:30,040 --> 00:25:32,920
正是 詹姆斯・林就是他的傀儡
Exactly. James Lim was his vanity case.

318
00:25:33,080 --> 00:25:35,200
比尔在办公桌前呆不住 你知道的
Bill hates sitting behind a desk. You know that.

319
00:25:35,360 --> 00:25:37,160
老是说他在别的什么地方
Always talking about being on the ground.

320
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:38,680
四十五岁时他在东德
45, he was in East Germany.

321
00:25:38,840 --> 00:25:41,440
五十二岁时在和鲁塞尼亚人喝酒
52, he's drinking vodka with the Ruskies.

322
00:25:41,560 --> 00:25:42,920
所以当詹姆斯・林出现时
So, when James Lim walked in,

323
00:25:43,080 --> 00:25:45,960
比尔决定他要亲自秘密操纵詹姆士
Bill decided that he's going to run him himself under the radar.

324
00:25:46,120 --> 00:25:48,040
所以他们就开始秘密会面了
So they start having these secret meetings.

325
00:25:48,200 --> 00:25:50,240
怀尔德・比尔自己做案件记录
Wild Bill's taking all the case notes himself.

326
00:25:50,400 --> 00:25:52,240
- 他们还达成交易 - 什么交易?
- They've got this deal. - What sort of deal?

327
00:25:52,360 --> 00:25:54,280
我不知道
I don't know.

328
00:25:54,440 --> 00:25:56,920
如果中情局想在这里建分局
If the CIA wanted to build a station here,

329
00:25:57,080 --> 00:25:59,560
他们就需要有个新加坡联络人来保护这片土地
they'd need a Singaporean contact to secure the land.

330
00:25:59,680 --> 00:26:02,840
拜托 山姆
Come on, Sam.

331
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:04,520
如果我知道那情报是真的
If I knew that information to be true,

332
00:26:04,680 --> 00:26:08,080
你真以为我会告诉你吗?
you really think I'd be talking to you about it?

333
00:26:08,240 --> 00:26:10,960
我只知道... 我也是从别人那打听到的
All I know ... and I got this second-hand 

334
00:26:11,120 --> 00:26:13,240
詹姆斯・林去见怀尔德・比尔
is that James Lim went to see Wild Bill

335
00:26:13,400 --> 00:26:16,080
是因为他觉得有个私家侦探在跟踪他
because he thought a private investigator was following him,

336
00:26:16,240 --> 00:26:18,160
而且可能还拍了他们一起的照片
and there may be some photos of them together.

337
00:26:18,320 --> 00:26:20,087
然后呢? 怀尔德・比尔做了什么?  
And? What did Wild Bill do? 

338
00:26:20,088 --> 00:26:21,088
我不知道
I don't know.

339
00:26:21,600 --> 00:26:23,640
我真不知道
I don't.

340
00:26:23,760 --> 00:26:25,120
那份文件不见了
The file's gone missing.

341
00:26:25,240 --> 00:26:27,320
被人毁了
Someone destroyed it.

342
00:26:27,440 --> 00:26:29,400
我们走吧
Let's go.

343
00:27:18,600 --> 00:27:20,880
卡拉汉 你也玩五百吗?
You play 500, Callaghan?

344
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:22,480
我玩另一个游戏
I've had a game.

345
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:23,960
绅士的游戏
A gentleman's game.

346
00:27:25,400 --> 00:27:26,880
不像扑克
Not like poker.

347
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:31,040
扑克是给粗人玩的
Poker's for assholes.

348
00:27:32,320 --> 00:27:33,880
是你杀了温斯顿・郑吗?
Did you kill Winston Cheng?

349
00:27:35,760 --> 00:27:37,960
没有 妈的 没有
No. Shit no.

350
00:27:42,080 --> 00:27:44,120
当然不是我
Of course not.

351
00:27:48,120 --> 00:27:50,000
不是
No.

352
00:27:50,120 --> 00:27:51,800
林告诉你
Lim had told you there'd been

353
00:27:51,960 --> 00:27:54,040
有人拍了你俩在一块的照片
photographs taken of the two of you together.

354
00:27:54,200 --> 00:27:57,120
对我而言 这没什么 我们是中情局的
It meant nothing to me. We're the CIA.

355
00:27:57,280 --> 00:27:59,920
我们有很多线人 他是其中之一 这没什么
We have informants. He was one of them. Big deal.

356
00:28:00,080 --> 00:28:02,440
就算登在<海峡时报>也不关我事
Publish them in The Straits Times for all I care.

357
00:28:02,600 --> 00:28:05,160
告诉所有人中情局正在秘密买地
Tell everyone the CIA is buying up land on the quiet

358
00:28:05,280 --> 00:28:06,880
建立秘密工作基地?
to build a covert operational base?

359
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:09,520
不是好事 但我可以否认
Not great, but deniable.

360
00:28:09,680 --> 00:28:12,240
- 不是为了詹姆斯・林 - 不是
- Not for James Lim. - No.

361
00:28:12,360 --> 00:28:14,240
他吓得要死
He was freaking out.

362
00:28:14,360 --> 00:28:16,040
他想从政
He wants to get into politics.

363
00:28:16,200 --> 00:28:18,240
和美国佬串通可不是什么好事
Not a good idea to be in bed with the Yanks,

364
00:28:18,360 --> 00:28:20,560
不过是他的问题 与我无关
but... his problem, not mine.

365
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:23,120
所以他雇了方去杀温斯顿?
So he hired Fong to kill Winston?

366
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:25,160
我原是这么想的
That's what I thought.

367
00:28:25,320 --> 00:28:28,440
直到今天
Until today. 

368
00:28:28,560 --> 00:28:30,200
谁杀了林?
Who had Lim killed?

369
00:28:30,320 --> 00:28:31,800
还有别的事
And there's something else.

370
00:28:31,960 --> 00:28:35,640
显而易见 某个人 某个耍纸牌的混蛋
Apparently, someone, some poker-playing asshole,

371
00:28:35,760 --> 00:28:37,160
一直在深究
has been doing some digging,

372
00:28:37,320 --> 00:28:39,280
发现了我都不知道的事
found out something even I didn't know about.

373
00:28:39,440 --> 00:28:40,533
什么事?  
What's that?  

374
00:28:40,534 --> 00:28:42,720
詹姆斯・林有个沉默的同伙
James Lim has a silent partner.

375
00:28:42,880 --> 00:28:45,360
- 有人在幕后资助他 - 是谁?
- Somebody's bankrolling him. - Who?

376
00:28:45,480 --> 00:28:47,720
高层不愿透露
Head office won't say.

377
00:28:47,880 --> 00:28:51,360
但他们肯定坏极了 因为 不管是谁
But they must be real bad, because, whoever it is,

378
00:28:51,520 --> 00:28:52,662
我也被牵扯其中 
my involvement with them, 

379
00:28:52,663 --> 00:28:54,520
即使是通过林这么一个第三方
even through a third party like Lim,

380
00:28:54,680 --> 00:28:56,720
也足以让我被遣送出局了
is enough to get me shipped out of here.

381
00:28:56,880 --> 00:29:00,480
中情局和什么人都有往来
There's not too many people the CIA won't do business with.

382
00:29:00,600 --> 00:29:03,400
俄罗斯人? 北越南人?
The Russians? North Vietnamese?

383
00:29:03,520 --> 00:29:05,320
我倒想知道
I'd love to know.

384
00:29:05,480 --> 00:29:07,007
无论谁 他们肯定有钱
Whoever it is, they've got the money 

385
00:29:07,008 --> 00:29:08,840
资助詹姆斯・林的地产贸易
to bankroll James Lim's land deals.

386
00:29:08,960 --> 00:29:10,840
还能保释方出狱
And to bail Fong out of jail.

387
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:13,920
也会为保守秘密而杀掉任何人
And they'll kill anyone to keep their involvement secret.

388
00:29:14,080 --> 00:29:17,800
只要找出这个人 就能找出谁杀了温斯顿
You find out who that is, you find out who murdered Winston.

389
00:29:21,600 --> 00:29:23,960
可是 卡拉汉...
But, Callaghan...

390
00:29:24,120 --> 00:29:27,120
...确保在他们发现你之前找到他们
...make sure you find them before they find you.

391
00:29:50,040 --> 00:29:53,360
山姆 你不会相信这个
Sam, you won't believe this.

392
00:31:20,880 --> 00:31:24,640
他进来的时候我正在看文件
I was looking at these documents when this man broke in.

393
00:31:24,800 --> 00:31:27,800
- 刚开始我还以为是你 - 不 这就是方
- At first I thought it was you. - No, that's Fong alright.

394
00:31:27,960 --> 00:31:30,160
毫无疑问他杀了温斯顿
And there's no doubt he killed Winston.

395
00:31:31,840 --> 00:31:36,480
所以他们杀温斯顿是因为这条信息
So they killed Winston for this information.

396
00:31:36,640 --> 00:31:40,360
我发现凯・索和詹姆斯・林
What I found out was that Kay Song and James Lim

397
00:31:40,520 --> 00:31:43,160
共事好多年 收买地产
had been in partnership for years, buying up land.

398
00:31:43,280 --> 00:31:44,880
凯・索?
Kay Song?

399
00:31:45,040 --> 00:31:47,640
可是红龙绝对不会和中情局搅合到一起
But the Red Dragons would never be in bed with the CIA.

400
00:31:47,800 --> 00:31:51,720
凯・索单独行动的 猛虎将军不知道
Kay Song is on his own. The Tiger General doesn't know.

401
00:31:51,840 --> 00:31:53,440
如果这就是凯・索的秘密... 
If that's Kay Song's secret...

402
00:31:55,560 --> 00:31:57,640
...凭这点就可以抓到他了
...that's how we get him.

403
00:31:57,800 --> 00:32:01,160
如果猛虎将军知道他的孙子和中情局有瓜葛
If the Tiger General knew his grandson was in bed with the CIA,

404
00:32:01,280 --> 00:32:02,640
他会杀了他的
he'd kill him.

405
00:32:22,040 --> 00:32:24,120
- 你肯定? - 绝对肯定
- Are you sure of this? - Absolutely.

406
00:32:24,280 --> 00:32:27,440
如果不这么做 凯・索会一直派人追踪我们
If we don't, Kay Song will keep sending people after us.

407
00:32:27,560 --> 00:32:29,640
你 我 和苏玲
You, me, Su Ling.

408
00:32:31,800 --> 00:32:35,080
我恳请跟杜凯见面
I respectfully seek an audience with Toh Kay.

409
00:32:35,240 --> 00:32:37,120
我们不想惹麻烦
Look, we don't want any trouble. 

410
00:32:37,280 --> 00:32:39,840
这有关于杀害我丈夫温斯顿・郑的凶手
This is about the murder of my husband, Winston Cheng.

411
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:41,675
女士 这不是你该来的地方 
Woman, this is not your place.  

412
00:32:41,676 --> 00:32:42,320
别动她!
Hey, leave her alone!

413
00:32:45,320 --> 00:32:47,200
来人呐！
Somebody help!

414
00:32:47,320 --> 00:32:49,800
快来人！
Somebody!

415
00:32:51,400 --> 00:32:53,240
你孙子骗了你
Your grandson is cheating you.

416
00:32:53,360 --> 00:32:55,240
他有秘密进账
He has secret accounts.

417
00:32:55,360 --> 00:32:56,920
他有私房钱
He has secret money.

418
00:32:57,040 --> 00:32:59,560
他在为自己工作
He's working for himself.

419
00:32:59,680 --> 00:33:01,560
我要听听他们的话
I will hear them.

420
00:33:06,640 --> 00:33:10,960
给自己做棺材 真是个好传统
It is a good tradition, making one's own coffin.

421
00:33:11,120 --> 00:33:14,960
我们的习惯是在派上用场好多年之前就做好
It is our custom to do so many years before it is needed.

422
00:33:15,120 --> 00:33:18,480
为死亡准备亦即为生命准备
To be prepared for death is to be prepared for life.

423
00:33:18,640 --> 00:33:21,120
你们国家有这种传统吗?
Do you have this custom in your country?

424
00:33:23,120 --> 00:33:24,600
应该有
You should.

425
00:33:24,720 --> 00:33:26,920
一个到处出漏子的人
A man who blunders here and there

426
00:33:27,080 --> 00:33:29,560
可能比想象得更早用上棺材
may need a coffin sooner than he thinks.

427
00:33:29,680 --> 00:33:31,560
说吧
Speak.

428
00:33:31,680 --> 00:33:33,560
不是你
Not you.

429
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:02,080
你和这个人在一起干什么?
What are you doing with this man?

430
00:34:02,240 --> 00:34:04,400
我和许多人都见过面啊
I have meetings with a lot of people.

431
00:34:04,560 --> 00:34:08,760
- 做生意的 家族领袖 - 私房钱呢?
- Businessmen, clan leaders. - Secret money?

432
00:34:10,520 --> 00:34:13,520
买片便宜地卖给美国人
For buying cheap land to sell to the Americans.

433
00:34:13,680 --> 00:34:15,520
-我们就要赚钱了 - 美国人?!
- We were going to make a fortune. - Americans?!

434
00:34:15,640 --> 00:34:17,600
是中情局
The CIA.

435
00:34:20,400 --> 00:34:24,000
我们控制着这座岛 一百多年了 
For over 100 years, we controlled this island.

436
00:34:24,120 --> 00:34:26,120
别人自以为有权有势
Others think they have the power.

437
00:34:26,240 --> 00:34:28,080
可他们来了又走
But they come, they go.

438
00:34:28,240 --> 00:34:30,560
英国人在这儿一个世纪 不也走了
The British, here for a century, they go too.

439
00:34:30,720 --> 00:34:33,760
这座岛终于是我们的了
Finally we have this island to ourselves.

440
00:34:33,920 --> 00:34:37,440
你还帮美国人掌权
And you help the Americans take power.

441
00:34:37,560 --> 00:34:39,000
我是为了你
I did it for you.

442
00:34:39,120 --> 00:34:41,720
你是为了自己
You did it for yourself.

443
00:34:41,840 --> 00:34:44,760
为了钱
For money.

444
00:34:48,640 --> 00:34:50,120
结束了
It's over.

445
00:34:51,920 --> 00:34:53,120
不要给我看

446
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:55,160
别让我看见尸体
Do not let me see the body.

447
00:34:59,360 --> 00:35:02,160
傻孩子
You stupid boy.

448
00:35:02,280 --> 00:35:05,160
你以为你能把我们全杀了?
You think you can kill us all?

449
00:35:05,280 --> 00:35:07,920
这倒是坚定了我的决心
This thinking confirms my decision.

450
00:35:08,040 --> 00:35:11,600
不 是坚定了我的
No. It confirms mine.

451
00:35:13,160 --> 00:35:15,000
像你这么老的人...
An old man like you...

452
00:35:15,120 --> 00:35:18,920
年老体衰
So frail, so weak.

453
00:35:19,040 --> 00:35:22,280
你疯了 我还能活很多年
You're mad. I have many years in me.

454
00:35:22,400 --> 00:35:25,040
可能会 可能不会
Maybe. Maybe not.

455
00:36:07,880 --> 00:36:09,360
你们走吧
You may leave.

456
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:15,960
我爷爷心脏病突发
My grandfather had a heart attack.

457
00:36:16,080 --> 00:36:17,680
我们有证人
We have witnesses.

458
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:27,200
把这噩耗告诉我们的人吧
Go tell our people the bad news.

459
00:36:34,400 --> 00:36:37,040
很抱歉你们目睹了这个令人悲伤的时刻
I'm sorry you had to be here for this sad day.

460
00:36:37,160 --> 00:36:40,560
郑夫人 山姆
Mrs Cheng, Sam.

461
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:45,160
现在让我一个人沉浸在悲痛中吧
You may now leave me to my grief.

462
00:37:02,480 --> 00:37:04,960
请进
Come in.

463
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:15,560
你想见我 先生
You wanted to see me, sir.

464
00:37:15,720 --> 00:37:18,640
我会很愿意永远不见你
I'd happily never set eyes on you again.

465
00:37:18,800 --> 00:37:21,640
不过当权者自作聪明
But the powers that be, in their wisdom,

466
00:37:21,800 --> 00:37:23,800
决定冻结所有的调动
have decided to put a freeze on all transfers.

467
00:37:25,400 --> 00:37:27,160
是的 先生
Yes, sir.

468
00:37:27,320 --> 00:37:29,240
好像我才该是那个评审的人吧
It seems my position's the one up for review.

469
00:37:34,040 --> 00:37:37,080
我不知道你做了什么 对谁亏欠
I don't know what you did or who you owe.

470
00:37:37,240 --> 00:37:41,720
但是记住... 和狗睡 就得忍着跳蚤
But remember this... you lay down with dogs, you get up with fleas.

471
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:46,920
你按照你的方式行事 先生
Well, you played the game your way, sir.

472
00:37:47,040 --> 00:37:48,920
和詹姆斯・林 进行土地贸易
With James Lim, with the land deal.

473
00:37:49,040 --> 00:37:50,920
我只不过做了该做的
I just did what I had to do.


474
00:37:52,360 --> 00:37:57,360
我所做的 都是为了这个组织为了我的祖国
Everything I did, I did for this organisation and for my country.

475
00:37:57,920 --> 00:38:00,920
如果他们解雇我... 当然 会很伤心
If they sack me... sure, it'll hurt.

476
00:38:02,200 --> 00:38:04,000
不过我可以每天照镜子
But I can look in the mirror every day.

477
00:38:04,160 --> 00:38:07,720
你觉得你照镜子会怎么样 哈里森?
What do you see when you look in the mirror, Harrison?

478
00:38:07,880 --> 00:38:11,240
因为总有一天 也许不是今天 不是明天
'Cause one day, maybe not today, not tomorrow,

479
00:38:11,400 --> 00:38:14,800
但是总有一天那玩意儿会把你活吞了
but one day that thing is going to eat you alive.

480
00:38:16,680 --> 00:38:18,760
谢谢你 先生
Thank you, sir.

481
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:21,000
你说对了一件事
Oh. You're right about one thing.

482
00:38:23,880 --> 00:38:25,760
不是今天
Not today.

483
00:39:02,720 --> 00:39:04,200
米勒少校
Major Miller.

484
00:39:06,080 --> 00:39:08,280
我刚收到电报
I just got the telegram.

485
00:39:10,320 --> 00:39:12,960
我下个月去华盛顿
I'm off to Washington next month.

486
00:39:21,640 --> 00:39:23,120
这是唯一的副本了?
This is the only copy?

487
00:39:24,440 --> 00:39:25,920
我们有交易的
We had a deal.

488
00:39:26,080 --> 00:39:31,060
你坚持你的原则 我坚持我的
You kept up your end. I kept up mine.

489
00:39:33,240 --> 00:39:35,600
也许我会在华盛顿见你
Maybe I'll see you in Washington.

490
00:39:37,160 --> 00:39:38,640
总有一天
One day.

491
00:39:38,760 --> 00:39:41,360
很可能
Good chance.

492
00:39:48,880 --> 00:39:50,480
希望她值得你这么做
I hope she's worth it.

493
00:40:35,480 --> 00:40:39,480
来来来 大家来喝一杯 开心点 来

494
00:40:39,480 --> 00:40:42,030
温斯顿是我们的好朋友

495
00:40:42,040 --> 00:40:44,120
温斯顿是个好男人
Winston is a good man.

496
00:40:45,020 --> 00:40:48,820
哎呀夫人 你不要太过悲伤 放轻松下 过来

497
00:40:48,820 --> 00:40:49,820
你讲啦

498
00:40:49,820 --> 00:40:51,820
哎呀你是他老婆

499
00:41:01,820 --> 00:41:03,279
今天中秋 中秋是个

500
00:41:03,280 --> 00:41:05,794
...合家团圆的日子 
...is for family, 

501
00:41:05,795 --> 00:41:08,080
你们就像我的家人一样
and you are like family to me.

502
00:41:09,160 --> 00:41:12,400
事实上 你们是我唯一的家人了
As a matter of fact, you are the only family I have.

503
00:41:12,520 --> 00:41:14,120
所以 谢谢你们
So, thank you.

504
00:41:15,720 --> 00:41:17,120
我讲什么

505
00:41:17,320 --> 00:41:18,520
喝酒喝酒

506
00:41:18,600 --> 00:41:21,880
我曾努力设想过温斯顿会说什么
Well, I tried to imagine what Winston would say,

507
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:24,360
然后我意识到他不过是整晚
and I realise he'd just be drinking

508
00:41:24,520 --> 00:41:27,200
喝酒跳舞讲笑话
and dancing and joking all night long,

509
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:30,120
所以今晚我希望你们也这么做
so this is what I want you to do tonight.

510
00:41:43,080 --> 00:41:47,440
# 我这颗心脏已经被伤了一千次 #
Ooh, this old heart of mine been broke a thousand times

511
00:41:47,600 --> 00:41:50,760
# 每次你离开我都以为你会留下来 #
Each time you break away I think you're gone to stay

512
00:41:50,920 --> 00:41:54,720
# 孤独的夜晚让记忆流淌 #
Lonely nights that come Memories that flow

513
00:41:54,880 --> 00:41:59,440
# 把你带回来一次次地伤害我 #
Bringing you back again Hurting me more and more

514
00:42:00,600 --> 00:42:05,600
# 也许向你表达我内心的爱是个错误 #
Maybe it's my mistake to show this love I feel inside

515
00:42:06,320 --> 00:42:09,920
# 因为日子一天天过去 #
'Cause each day that passes by

516
